1
00:00:50,925 --> 00:00:54,387
Chief, is it okay if I continue assisting
with the investigation?

2
00:00:55,070 --> 00:00:56,114
Of course.

3
00:00:56,139 --> 00:00:59,266
We need your skills for cases like this.

4
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:02,394
Potassium Cyanide
inhibits cellular respiration,

5
00:01:02,395 --> 00:01:05,440
preventing tissues
from using oxygen from the blood.

6
00:01:05,690 --> 00:01:08,776
Anyone who ingests,
it will show bluish lips.

7
00:01:08,777 --> 00:01:10,486
They’re the only ones
who had access to the victim.

8
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:11,653
Was it super traffic?

9
00:01:11,654 --> 00:01:12,696
Yeah, totally!

10
00:01:12,697 --> 00:01:14,406
Can we just move to a different table?

11
00:01:14,407 --> 00:01:16,326
- I’m just going to the CR.
- Yeah, sure.

12
00:01:18,119 --> 00:01:20,205
Yeah! It was me!

13
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:23,458
I'm the one who poisoned Draco.

14
00:01:25,710 --> 00:01:27,253
There’s no more threat to you, Lori.

15
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:29,464
You're safe.

16
00:01:31,299 --> 00:01:32,424
- Come with us.
- No.

17
00:01:32,425 --> 00:01:35,553
- Trust me.
- Get away from me.

18
00:01:36,679 --> 00:01:38,031
Lorelei! Lorelei!

19
00:01:38,056 --> 00:01:39,057
Lorelei!

20
00:01:39,849 --> 00:01:40,742
Lorelei!

21
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:41,851
Lorelei.

22
00:01:44,819 --> 00:01:46,279
Loki...

23
00:01:56,032 --> 00:01:57,992
Hey, you there!

24
00:01:58,993 --> 00:02:00,662
Why don’t we play a game?

25
00:02:01,412 --> 00:02:03,039
Can’t find him anywhere?

26
00:02:03,665 --> 00:02:05,125
Oh, what a shame!

27
00:02:05,759 --> 00:02:07,168
I will give you time.

28
00:02:08,169 --> 00:02:10,213
Is 45 minutes fine?

29
00:02:11,339 --> 00:02:15,218
Better hurry up
'cause his life is on the line!

30
00:02:16,094 --> 00:02:17,886
Find the coordinates.

31
00:02:17,887 --> 00:02:19,681
Get out of that square.

32
00:02:20,181 --> 00:02:23,852
Then take one step back
and see the answer.

33
00:02:24,686 --> 00:02:25,687
14,

34
00:02:26,229 --> 00:02:27,355
24,

35
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:28,815
21,

36
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:30,400
14,

37
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:31,901
31,

38
00:02:32,318 --> 00:02:33,570
45,

39
00:02:33,862 --> 00:02:35,071
24,

40
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:36,656
21,

41
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,074
23,

42
00:02:38,449 --> 00:02:39,617
55,

43
00:02:40,076 --> 00:02:41,452
33.

44
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:44,998
Missing…

45
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:47,958
Loki is missing?

46
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:48,960
What?

47
00:02:50,461 --> 00:02:53,923
I was looking forward to spending
the afternoon with him.

48
00:02:54,424 --> 00:02:57,677
Why did it have to be him? Why not you?

49
00:02:57,802 --> 00:02:58,803
Huh?

50
00:02:59,345 --> 00:03:01,054
And I’m the one you want gone?

51
00:03:01,055 --> 00:03:03,266
You’re the new one in this club.

52
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:08,730
What are you in this club, decoration?

53
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:13,860
You know what,
Loki and I can get along better.

54
00:03:13,943 --> 00:03:17,280
We actually had a great time
at lunch earlier.

55
00:03:18,489 --> 00:03:21,909
And he had to treat me
because I beat him at chess.

56
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:26,705
My God, we don’t have time
to talk about how full you got at lunch.

57
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:28,208
We need to find him!

58
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:34,339
Maybe this is Moriarty.

59
00:03:36,716 --> 00:03:40,094
Lorelei! What, you're just staring there?

60
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:44,181
You know what, let’s report
Loki’s disappearance to campus police.

61
00:03:44,182 --> 00:03:45,390
No, no.

62
00:03:45,391 --> 00:03:50,563
We need to decode this to find Loki
because we only have 45 minutes!

63
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:54,734
Oh, you think you can decode the code?

64
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:57,320
Loki’s the only one who can.

65
00:03:57,362 --> 00:03:59,239
That’s why we have to do this together!

66
00:03:59,364 --> 00:04:01,073
And for the record,

67
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:05,203
you know, I've managed to solve a case
with minimal help from him.

68
00:04:05,328 --> 00:04:06,329
What about you?

69
00:04:06,621 --> 00:04:09,540
Is acting cute for Loki all you can do?

70
00:04:11,417 --> 00:04:13,628
Why did you even join this club, anyway?

71
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:16,589
Whatever. Give me that!

72
00:04:18,007 --> 00:04:20,510
You know what?
Let’s report this to campus police.

73
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:21,844
My gosh.

74
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:23,346
Jamie! Give me that!

75
00:04:23,721 --> 00:04:25,847
This is a waste of time. We can do this.

76
00:04:25,848 --> 00:04:27,182
Exactly. This is a waste of time.

77
00:04:27,183 --> 00:04:29,643
- Why don’t we report this to the police?
- Give it to me. I’ll do it.

78
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:31,186
- Give it to me!
- Come on!

79
00:04:31,187 --> 00:04:32,730
- Lori, give me that!
- Oh, my!

80
00:04:33,123 --> 00:04:34,291
- Give me that!
- Give me that!

81
00:04:35,316 --> 00:04:36,985
Oh, my God!

82
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,820
Look what you did!

83
00:04:38,903 --> 00:04:41,406
We only have half the code.

84
00:04:41,781 --> 00:04:44,575
It's all smudged. What are we gonna do?

85
00:04:45,159 --> 00:04:46,326
It’s your fault.

86
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:48,037
- My fault?
- Yes.

87
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:50,123
It’s your fault.

88
00:04:50,623 --> 00:04:52,083
How is this my fault?

89
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,460
Whatever. But it’s your fault.

90
00:04:54,585 --> 00:04:57,797
That's good, so we'll end up
with the campus police.

91
00:04:59,716 --> 00:05:02,719
By the way,
I’ve memorized the numbers.

92
00:05:03,052 --> 00:05:05,305
But I’m not telling you.

93
00:05:05,388 --> 00:05:06,472
What?

94
00:05:07,849 --> 00:05:09,642
- Bye, Lori!
- Jamie!

95
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:11,394
Jamie!

96
00:05:11,517 --> 00:05:13,769
♪ Shadows ♪

97
00:05:14,435 --> 00:05:17,146
♪ in the dark are crawling. ♪

98
00:05:17,636 --> 00:05:21,963
♪ Keeping watch and barring your way. ♪

99
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:25,533
♪ As if the line could not be crossed. ♪

100
00:05:26,140 --> 00:05:29,642
♪ To every scream and every tremor. ♪

101
00:05:29,667 --> 00:05:32,836
♪ These walls remain the only witness. ♪

102
00:05:32,861 --> 00:05:35,821
♪ Every noise is etched in here. ♪

103
00:05:35,846 --> 00:05:40,351
♪ Like fire and ammunition
for your memory. ♪

104
00:05:41,724 --> 00:05:43,851
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

105
00:05:45,368 --> 00:05:47,745
♪ The threats poised to strike. ♪

106
00:05:48,634 --> 00:05:52,305
♪ For this world ♪

107
00:05:52,980 --> 00:05:55,607
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

108
00:05:55,632 --> 00:05:58,093
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

109
00:05:58,913 --> 00:06:01,040
♪ Open up your eyes. ♪

110
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:06,324
♪ For this world ♪

111
00:06:06,853 --> 00:06:09,552
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

112
00:06:09,577 --> 00:06:14,415
♪ Heed the warnings ♪

113
00:06:15,783 --> 00:06:16,784
Jamie!

114
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:19,212
Please! Just give me the numbers!

115
00:06:19,837 --> 00:06:22,757
If you remember, then write them on paper.

116
00:06:22,965 --> 00:06:24,509
Please, we’re running out of time!

117
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:26,344
Don’t you get it, Lorelei?

118
00:06:26,594 --> 00:06:27,928
We’ll just waste more time

119
00:06:27,929 --> 00:06:31,723
if we keep trying to crack a code
that’s not even our expertise.

120
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:36,436
But if we report this to campus police,
we can’t be sure they’ll believe us.

121
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:38,648
They might think
that this is some stupid prank!

122
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:41,316
Trust me on this, Jamie,
when I'm telling you

123
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:43,736
that this is not your ordinary case.

124
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:45,196
There’s somebody behind this!

125
00:06:45,571 --> 00:06:46,572
Who?

126
00:06:46,948 --> 00:06:49,699
Look, I can’t tell you right now, okay?

127
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:51,368
But you might not be aware of this,

128
00:06:51,369 --> 00:06:53,120
but here in the Q.E.D. Club,

129
00:06:53,121 --> 00:06:55,581
we have a process,
and we have to work together.

130
00:06:56,874 --> 00:07:00,460
So are you saying
I’m just a newbie in your club?

131
00:07:00,461 --> 00:07:01,628
Well, yes!

132
00:07:01,629 --> 00:07:04,214
I mean, I’m just saying we have a process.

133
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:07,384
And ever since you came in,
you’ve been ruining that process!

134
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:10,555
Because you’re here
trying to take control over everything!

135
00:07:11,305 --> 00:07:15,518
Oh, so this is my fault now?

136
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:18,062
My God, Jamie! This is not about you!

137
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:21,023
This is about Loki!
And we have to save him!

138
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:24,860
I want to save Loki too!
What do you think of me?

139
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:28,531
I just think
that we have to go to the police.

140
00:07:29,657 --> 00:07:35,580
Look, I just wanna get
all the possible help to find Loki.

141
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,794
Okay. Fine.

142
00:07:42,378 --> 00:07:43,379
You’re right.

143
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:46,716
Chief Estrada might be able to help us.

144
00:07:47,508 --> 00:07:48,509
Let’s go?

145
00:07:51,929 --> 00:07:52,972
Let's go.

146
00:07:57,518 --> 00:07:58,977
- Officer! Officer!
- Officer!

147
00:07:58,978 --> 00:08:00,979
- Can we speak to...
- There’s a missing student.

148
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:03,523
- Can we speak to Chief Estrada?
- Someone left us a note.

149
00:08:03,524 --> 00:08:05,485
- My friend is missing.
- Wait, wait. Hold on!

150
00:08:05,776 --> 00:08:06,777
Take a breath first.

151
00:08:07,612 --> 00:08:09,946
Can we speak to Chief Estrada?

152
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:12,616
Oh, the chief isn’t here right now.

153
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:14,242
He has a meeting with the president.

154
00:08:14,243 --> 00:08:17,954
Please? Can you call him?
This is an emergency.

155
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:21,501
A student is missing.
Someone left us a note.

156
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:23,769
What’s the name of the missing student?

157
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:25,253
- Loki Mendez!
- Loki Mendez!

158
00:08:25,254 --> 00:08:27,548
Oh, Loki.

159
00:08:27,673 --> 00:08:30,176
Please, officer,
maybe you can do something about this.

160
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:33,554
Oh, I’m afraid that’s not possible. Sorry.

161
00:08:33,721 --> 00:08:35,306
What should we do?

162
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:42,854
- Just wait about 24 hours before you act.
- Twenty-four hours?

163
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:44,940
Because that note might just be a prank.

164
00:08:44,941 --> 00:08:46,358
There have been
a lot of cases like that lately.

165
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:49,987
But, officer, a lot of crimes
have been happening at the university.

166
00:08:50,238 --> 00:08:54,074
We can’t wait 24 hours. Look at this note.

167
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:57,537
We were only given 40 minutes
to find our friend.

168
00:08:57,912 --> 00:09:01,582
What if this isn’t a prank
and he’s in danger?

169
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:04,168
Whose responsibility is that?

170
00:09:04,502 --> 00:09:06,044
And based on my research,

171
00:09:06,045 --> 00:09:09,924
you don’t need to wait 24 hours
for reports like this.

172
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:13,052
Immediate action is needed.
That’s the police’s duty!

173
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:14,637
I’m sorry, there’s nothing I can do.

174
00:09:18,307 --> 00:09:20,726
Officer, please.

175
00:09:21,352 --> 00:09:23,353
If I don’t find him,

176
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:27,149
I might lose my chance
to tell the one I love…

177
00:09:28,150 --> 00:09:29,944
that I love him too.

178
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:39,452
Is that so? Alright, I’ll call
a search team now for your friend.

179
00:09:39,453 --> 00:09:40,580
Right now?

180
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:42,831
We have a process here, okay?

181
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:44,917
You’re not the only ones
we’re handling here.

182
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:48,045
If I say I’ll call you, I’ll call you.

183
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:53,759
Okay, officer. That’s a big help to us.

184
00:09:54,093 --> 00:09:58,472
It’s nothing. In about ten minutes,
the search team will be there, okay?

185
00:09:59,849 --> 00:10:01,601
Thank you.

186
00:10:02,012 --> 00:10:03,180
Okay, okay.

187
00:10:09,817 --> 00:10:13,029
At least they’re sending
a search team for Loki.

188
00:10:13,195 --> 00:10:15,990
But they said it’ll take ten minutes
before they deploy.

189
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:21,078
See? We only have 30 minutes left.

190
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:24,360
I doubt they’ll find Loki
with that time frame.

191
00:10:25,249 --> 00:10:28,544
Jamie, what if they find Loki
but it’s already too late?

192
00:10:42,099 --> 00:10:46,604
Lorelei, they’re police.
They know what they’re doing.

193
00:10:46,854 --> 00:10:50,733
But I don’t want to wait, okay?
Time’s running, Jamie.

194
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:52,901
The police can search at the same time.

195
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:56,030
But we should do something
to save Loki too.

196
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:57,698
Every second counts!

197
00:11:01,911 --> 00:11:05,498
Come on, we can do this.
We can save Loki!

198
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:09,251
You're right. Fine.

199
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:11,128
But how?

200
00:11:11,253 --> 00:11:13,047
How do we crack the code?

201
00:11:13,297 --> 00:11:15,466
Only Loki can do that!

202
00:11:19,053 --> 00:11:20,971
Aside from Loki,

203
00:11:21,972 --> 00:11:24,517
who else is capable of...

204
00:11:25,726 --> 00:11:27,311
cracking this code?

205
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:31,440
Someone who’s also interested in codes.

206
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:35,653
If you need help,
especially with numbers, I can help.

207
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:42,493
Jamie, are you close with Stein Alberts?

208
00:11:45,746 --> 00:11:46,746
Stein.

209
00:11:48,082 --> 00:11:48,958
Hey, Jamie!

210
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:51,168
Glad you made it back
to the Repertory Club.

211
00:11:52,795 --> 00:11:55,005
Actually, I'm taking a break.

212
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:58,134
You’re the one we came here for.

213
00:11:58,718 --> 00:11:59,719
Me?

214
00:12:00,344 --> 00:12:02,388
Sorry to bother you, Stein, but…

215
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:06,399
you’re the only one
we can think of turning to.

216
00:12:07,879 --> 00:12:09,881
Can you crack that code?

217
00:12:21,657 --> 00:12:22,658
No problem!

218
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:26,162
The least I can do is help the person
who saved my life.

219
00:12:28,831 --> 00:12:32,501
At least, I’m not the suspect.

220
00:12:47,057 --> 00:12:48,058
Did you get it?

221
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:52,438
Do you know the Polybius square?

222
00:12:57,526 --> 00:13:00,529
Polybius was a Greek historian
during the Hellenistic period.

223
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:04,784
He was responsible
for developing a tool for cryptography.

224
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:06,452
Here.

225
00:13:07,161 --> 00:13:08,454
The Polybius square.

226
00:13:10,247 --> 00:13:13,458
All the letters of the alphabet
are arranged from left to right,

227
00:13:13,459 --> 00:13:16,086
and top to bottom
in a five-by-five square.

228
00:13:16,587 --> 00:13:18,964
To make all the letters
of the alphabet fit,

229
00:13:19,131 --> 00:13:21,217
I and J are combined in a single cell.

230
00:13:22,092 --> 00:13:25,429
Now, the rows and columns together

231
00:13:25,471 --> 00:13:28,808
represent each letter’s position
in the grid.

232
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:30,184
For example,

233
00:13:30,392 --> 00:13:35,356
14 represents D
while 24 represents letter I or J.

234
00:13:35,773 --> 00:13:38,107
The left digit indicates the row,

235
00:13:38,108 --> 00:13:40,861
while the right digit
indicates the column.

236
00:13:41,570 --> 00:13:44,240
It’s like you’re just using
map coordinates.

237
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:46,074
Coordinates?

238
00:13:47,368 --> 00:13:48,702
Like on a chessboard.

239
00:13:51,372 --> 00:13:55,768
Oh, if you have any questions
or need clarification, let me know.

240
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:57,378
Since you’re the Q.E.D. Club,

241
00:13:57,753 --> 00:13:59,755
you should be able
to crack that code on your own.

242
00:14:00,673 --> 00:14:02,328
Sorry, because I still have class.

243
00:14:02,353 --> 00:14:04,740
We’re good now, Stein. Thank you.

244
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:06,387
No worries.

245
00:14:16,397 --> 00:14:18,023
Time check, Lorelei.

246
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:19,787
Twenty minutes left.

247
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:24,864
55 is Z.

248
00:14:25,698 --> 00:14:27,366
33 is N.

249
00:14:28,158 --> 00:14:29,159
Wait.

250
00:14:30,077 --> 00:14:31,245
Why is it like that?

251
00:14:32,371 --> 00:14:33,706
It doesn’t make sense.

252
00:14:34,957 --> 00:14:37,459
Maybe we just used the wrong cipher.

253
00:14:37,793 --> 00:14:38,794
No.

254
00:14:39,169 --> 00:14:40,337
That’s Stein.

255
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:43,047
He seems pretty confident
about the Polybius square.

256
00:14:43,048 --> 00:14:44,466
So what comes out?

257
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:46,475
Still something
we can’t make sense of, right?

258
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:49,471
We just wasted time going to Stein.

259
00:14:50,890 --> 00:14:53,017
Wait, Jamie. Let me think.

260
00:14:53,559 --> 00:14:54,560
Okay.

261
00:14:55,603 --> 00:14:56,854
Polybius square.

262
00:14:58,564 --> 00:14:59,565
Coordinates.

263
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,026
Chessboard.

264
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:06,196
What are we missing?

265
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:11,784
Maybe we really just wasted time
going to Stein.

266
00:15:11,785 --> 00:15:15,331
Hello? You’re the one
who suggested we go to him, right?

267
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:17,832
I thought he could help us,
that’s why I agreed...

268
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,793
Can we not blame each other?

269
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:23,172
Okay, can we just focus
on helping each other out?

270
00:15:23,797 --> 00:15:25,966
Please, for Loki’s sake.

271
00:15:27,217 --> 00:15:28,761
At least let’s do it for him.

272
00:15:29,803 --> 00:15:30,804
Sorry.

273
00:15:32,348 --> 00:15:35,059
Okay, can you help me out here?

274
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:39,897
Can you recite the whole riddle
from the start?

275
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:43,359
Hey, you there!

276
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:45,444
Why don’t we play a game?

277
00:15:45,861 --> 00:15:47,363
Can’t find him anywhere?

278
00:15:48,322 --> 00:15:49,490
Oh, what a shame!

279
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:52,743
Okay, there's nothing special there.

280
00:15:53,577 --> 00:15:56,663
They just want us to know
they want to play.

281
00:15:56,664 --> 00:15:58,332
Go on, Jamie.

282
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:00,626
I will give you time.

283
00:16:01,085 --> 00:16:03,003
Is 45 minutes fine?

284
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:05,130
Better hurry up

285
00:16:05,839 --> 00:16:07,716
‘cause his life in on the line.

286
00:16:09,718 --> 00:16:12,638
Just time and a threat.

287
00:16:13,430 --> 00:16:14,431
Continue.

288
00:16:14,556 --> 00:16:16,058
Find the coordinates.

289
00:16:16,392 --> 00:16:18,394
Get out of that square.

290
00:16:20,604 --> 00:16:22,397
Okay. Stein’s right.

291
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:23,440
Polybius square.

292
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:24,858
Continue.

293
00:16:25,401 --> 00:16:28,570
Then take one step back
and see the answer.

294
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:33,826
One step back.

295
00:16:37,287 --> 00:16:38,288
C,

296
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:41,125
H,

297
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:44,086
E,

298
00:16:45,129 --> 00:16:46,130
C,

299
00:16:47,339 --> 00:16:48,340
K,

300
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:50,926
T, H.

301
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:52,511
E,

302
00:16:53,053 --> 00:16:54,054
G,

303
00:16:54,763 --> 00:16:56,181
Y, M.

304
00:17:00,602 --> 00:17:01,770
One step back.

305
00:17:05,232 --> 00:17:06,233
Look here.

306
00:17:07,067 --> 00:17:08,068
No way!

307
00:17:08,402 --> 00:17:11,363
I can’t believe you solved it.

308
00:17:11,697 --> 00:17:13,615
Let’s go! We don’t have much time!

309
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,535
Let’s go, Jamie!

310
00:17:21,123 --> 00:17:24,418
Lori, we only have five minutes left.

311
00:17:28,213 --> 00:17:30,632
We only have five minutes to find Loki.

312
00:17:35,929 --> 00:17:38,306
Let’s go! Let’s check every room here.

313
00:17:38,307 --> 00:17:39,433
Wait, Jamie!

314
00:17:39,683 --> 00:17:43,604
We’ll run out of time
if we check every room here.

315
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:47,191
Do you have any better idea?

316
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:51,111
Do you know what places are in here?

317
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:56,033
We need to deduce where they took Loki.

318
00:17:56,784 --> 00:18:00,704
They probably took him
somewhere students don’t go.

319
00:18:10,631 --> 00:18:11,632
Jamie.

320
00:18:12,049 --> 00:18:16,804
Jamie, this is your opportunity
to use your photographic memory.

321
00:18:19,681 --> 00:18:25,187
Can you enumerate all the places
around this area for me?

322
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:39,243
There’s a locker room,
the basketball court,

323
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:41,662
the equipment room, the bathrooms,

324
00:18:42,581 --> 00:18:43,999
and the lounge!

325
00:18:44,373 --> 00:18:45,749
Where’s the storage room?

326
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:47,126
It’s at the end!

327
00:19:02,182 --> 00:19:03,851
Lori! Wait for me!

328
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:36,884
Very well played!

329
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:39,761
Loki?

330
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:43,891
You took your time, Lorelei and Jamie.

331
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:46,476
I thought you wouldn’t find me.

332
00:19:47,352 --> 00:19:48,395
Loki…

333
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:50,480
I'm glad you're safe.

334
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:54,359
So you weren’t actually kidnapped?

335
00:19:57,196 --> 00:19:58,697
You may call it a test.

336
00:19:59,531 --> 00:20:03,076
I wanted to see
if you could solve a case without me.

337
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:05,662
And if you guys can work together.

338
00:20:06,747 --> 00:20:08,999
It turned out pretty well, didn’t it?

339
00:20:10,792 --> 00:20:11,835
The riddle,

340
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:14,338
the time limit,

341
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:15,881
the code.

342
00:20:16,340 --> 00:20:17,341
Well played.

343
00:20:17,925 --> 00:20:19,176
Very well played.

344
00:20:21,678 --> 00:20:22,679
Well...

345
00:20:23,513 --> 00:20:24,932
what did you expect from me?

346
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:35,943
What the hell, Lorelei?

347
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:37,903
Why did you slap him?

348
00:20:38,153 --> 00:20:40,572
I thought Moriarty had kidnapped you!

349
00:20:41,323 --> 00:20:43,158
Did you really think this is funny?

350
00:20:43,784 --> 00:20:46,453
Moriarty? Who’s that?

351
00:20:46,912 --> 00:20:48,330
Think it through next time.

352
00:20:48,705 --> 00:20:51,208
Not everyone is entertained by your jokes!

353
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:01,426
Lorelei!

354
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:06,223
What was that? What did you do to Loki?

355
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:09,434
And who is this Moriarty
you’re talking about?

356
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:12,812
What does that have to do
with this and Loki?

357
00:21:12,813 --> 00:21:14,356
Jamie, not now, please.

358
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:17,817
If you want, just go back inside
and hug Loki again.

359
00:21:17,818 --> 00:21:18,818
Huh?

360
00:21:19,069 --> 00:21:22,071
Is this the reason
why you snapped earlier?

361
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:23,991
Because you’re jealous of us?

362
00:21:24,574 --> 00:21:25,575
What?

363
00:21:26,285 --> 00:21:28,412
You think I’m that shallow?

364
00:21:29,246 --> 00:21:30,080
Really?

365
00:21:30,081 --> 00:21:32,457
So why did you just do it then, huh?

366
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:37,045
Look, Jamie, okay. It’s been a long day.

367
00:21:37,671 --> 00:21:39,797
I don’t want to argue with you, alright?

368
00:21:39,798 --> 00:21:42,967
Thanks so much for your help
in finding Loki. Really.

369
00:21:42,968 --> 00:21:44,385
And I think we should call it a day.

370
00:21:44,386 --> 00:21:46,721
- Let's just rest...
- What? We're both tired.

371
00:21:46,722 --> 00:21:49,640
And that’s no reason to slap Loki!

372
00:21:49,641 --> 00:21:51,560
Why did you slap Loki?

373
00:21:53,312 --> 00:21:54,730
Do you hear that?

374
00:21:55,272 --> 00:21:56,315
Which one?

375
00:21:57,190 --> 00:21:58,233
The melody.

376
00:21:59,901 --> 00:22:02,112
From a phone. Somewhere here.

377
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:09,161
Do you hear that?

378
00:22:09,786 --> 00:22:11,413
Yeah, I heard it earlier. So what?

379
00:22:11,913 --> 00:22:13,790
Why are you switching topics?

380
00:22:16,501 --> 00:22:19,171
Lorelei! What?
Just standing there staring?

381
00:22:19,877 --> 00:22:22,463
What? You’re not gonna talk to me?

382
00:22:25,385 --> 00:22:26,386
Lorelei!

383
00:22:26,678 --> 00:22:29,306
Where are you going now? You keep leaving!

384
00:22:29,848 --> 00:22:31,641
Oh, my God. This is crazy.

385
00:23:47,384 --> 00:23:49,766
Are you really that insensitive, Loki?

386
00:23:52,305 --> 00:23:55,946
Like you enjoy playing
with other people’s emotions.

387
00:24:06,945 --> 00:24:09,114
Do you always see us
as just an experiment?

388
00:24:14,119 --> 00:24:15,119
What?

389
00:24:16,037 --> 00:24:17,038
No answer?

390
00:24:21,042 --> 00:24:22,919
You’re just going to let this slide again?

391
00:24:27,883 --> 00:24:29,885
There’ll be a new case again,

392
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:33,847
and this issue will just be forgotten.

393
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:36,892
- And then...
- Contrary to your belief...

394
00:24:38,059 --> 00:24:40,395
I do take notes on the things you tell me.

395
00:24:43,398 --> 00:24:45,025
I don’t forget that.

396
00:24:47,152 --> 00:24:49,863
And you're right
that you found my experiment hurtful.

397
00:24:51,656 --> 00:24:54,618
I suppose I have to say...

398
00:24:55,619 --> 00:24:56,620
I'm sorry.

399
00:24:58,497 --> 00:25:00,665
You’re really making this a pattern, huh?

400
00:25:01,458 --> 00:25:02,918
When you make a mistake,

401
00:25:03,335 --> 00:25:05,587
you just say sorry
for the sake of saying it.

402
00:25:07,172 --> 00:25:09,716
Even now, you still can’t understand it?

403
00:25:10,133 --> 00:25:11,550
That’s not the point of apologizing.

404
00:25:11,551 --> 00:25:13,220
I don’t think I did anything wrong.

405
00:25:14,054 --> 00:25:15,514
I didn’t hurt anyone.

406
00:25:16,723 --> 00:25:17,723
But...

407
00:25:17,891 --> 00:25:21,978
I apologized
in case my actions offended you.

408
00:25:25,385 --> 00:25:26,907
Do you hear yourself?

409
00:25:29,569 --> 00:25:31,915
Are you really that oblivious, Loki?

410
00:25:33,490 --> 00:25:35,282
I’m grateful you saved my life.

411
00:25:36,498 --> 00:25:37,499
Twice.

412
00:25:39,287 --> 00:25:41,414
I owe you a lot.

413
00:25:43,291 --> 00:25:45,335
But to kidnap yourself

414
00:25:45,961 --> 00:25:48,088
after we both experienced danger?

415
00:25:49,923 --> 00:25:51,758
We almost died.

416
00:25:53,093 --> 00:25:54,427
Really, Loki?

417
00:25:56,054 --> 00:25:58,306
That’s exactly the point of the test.

418
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:02,936
We must always be ready
for the danger ahead.

419
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:06,321
And you...

420
00:26:06,982 --> 00:26:08,525
handled it perfectly.

421
00:26:11,611 --> 00:26:12,612
Test?

422
00:26:13,113 --> 00:26:14,114
Test...

423
00:26:14,406 --> 00:26:16,408
It’s always tests with you, Loki.

424
00:26:17,867 --> 00:26:19,703
But that’s not the point.

425
00:26:21,997 --> 00:26:24,624
I was worried sick about you.

426
00:26:27,210 --> 00:26:30,338
I’ve been going crazy here
thinking if you’re okay.

427
00:26:32,048 --> 00:26:34,259
If something bad happened to you.

428
00:26:35,135 --> 00:26:37,304
If Moriarty was hurting you,

429
00:26:37,929 --> 00:26:39,472
or whoever’s out there.

430
00:26:42,142 --> 00:26:45,644
And you’re saying
I was just offended by what you did,

431
00:26:45,645 --> 00:26:47,230
which you think wasn’t wrong?

432
00:26:52,360 --> 00:26:55,155
You take the people around you
for granted.

433
00:26:57,115 --> 00:27:00,994
That’s why sometimes I wonder
if you’re still worth worrying about.

434
00:27:02,704 --> 00:27:03,997
Because ever since,

435
00:27:05,206 --> 00:27:08,627
you’ve never cared
about other people’s feelings.

436
00:27:16,468 --> 00:27:18,094
About how I feel.

437
00:27:44,120 --> 00:27:45,120
Lori.

438
00:27:45,372 --> 00:27:46,414
How are you?

439
00:27:50,919 --> 00:27:52,087
That’s deep.

440
00:27:53,421 --> 00:27:55,131
Does that mean you’re not okay?

441
00:27:56,216 --> 00:27:57,217
A little.

442
00:27:58,009 --> 00:27:59,010
Do you get it?

443
00:27:59,928 --> 00:28:02,222
You’re okay,

444
00:28:03,515 --> 00:28:04,849
you’re still alive,

445
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:07,686
you’re still doing good at school, but...

446
00:28:09,020 --> 00:28:10,855
you’re still anxious because...

447
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:13,274
so many bad things are happening.

448
00:28:14,442 --> 00:28:15,777
I get you, girl.

449
00:28:16,569 --> 00:28:19,572
It’s really hard being caught
in the middle of your emotions.

450
00:28:20,156 --> 00:28:22,784
You don’t even know
which one to fully give in to.

451
00:28:23,952 --> 00:28:25,078
That’s so true.

452
00:28:25,745 --> 00:28:26,746
How about you?

453
00:28:27,539 --> 00:28:28,540
How are you?

454
00:28:29,999 --> 00:28:31,334
I’m doing okay.

455
00:28:32,377 --> 00:28:35,839
I’m also bothered
by what’s happening, but...

456
00:28:36,881 --> 00:28:38,133
I choose to be okay.

457
00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:40,051
Less stress too.

458
00:28:40,593 --> 00:28:45,223
Besides, the school’s doing everything
to protect students.

459
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:48,226
That’s why we have campus police.

460
00:29:17,046 --> 00:29:20,508
I just want to apologize
for slapping you yesterday.

461
00:29:21,634 --> 00:29:25,472
What I did was completely wrong
and uncalled for.

462
00:29:29,809 --> 00:29:31,186
Apology accepted.

463
00:29:35,231 --> 00:29:37,525
I still stand by what I said yesterday.

464
00:29:38,985 --> 00:29:41,571
I hope you think about what I said.

465
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:47,368
Oh, you’re here.

466
00:29:47,827 --> 00:29:49,329
Did you get some rest?

467
00:29:51,998 --> 00:29:53,583
Can I confront you now?

468
00:29:54,083 --> 00:29:55,126
It’s up to you.

469
00:29:55,835 --> 00:29:58,421
But I’m not here to argue with you.

470
00:30:03,176 --> 00:30:04,177
Wow.

471
00:30:04,928 --> 00:30:07,263
Is what you’re about to say confidential?

472
00:30:07,472 --> 00:30:10,099
Yes. So listen carefully.

473
00:30:16,231 --> 00:30:19,150
Last night, as I left the gym,

474
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:24,280
I heard the alphanumeric dial tones
of the phone

475
00:30:24,739 --> 00:30:26,658
playing Mary Had a Little Lamb.

476
00:30:29,619 --> 00:30:31,329
When I followed the sound,

477
00:30:31,913 --> 00:30:35,333
I saw a man in the gym
talking on the phone.

478
00:30:36,167 --> 00:30:39,003
- Hello?
- He's a campus police officer, in uniform.

479
00:30:39,671 --> 00:30:41,088
I couldn’t see his face.

480
00:30:41,089 --> 00:30:43,842
- Alright.
- But his build looked familiar.

481
00:30:44,801 --> 00:30:46,594
So I followed him.

482
00:30:51,391 --> 00:30:54,894
I was hoping he’d lead me to Moriarty.

483
00:31:19,057 --> 00:31:23,103
But I was even more surprised
when he took off his hat.

484
00:31:24,465 --> 00:31:25,466
Why?

485
00:31:26,259 --> 00:31:27,260
Who was it?

486
00:31:29,517 --> 00:31:31,644
It was Officer Bastien Montreal.

487
00:31:53,286 --> 00:31:54,579
Bastien Montreal.

488
00:31:56,372 --> 00:31:58,625
The rookie officer from campus police.

489
00:31:59,751 --> 00:32:01,753
Yeah. Right?

490
00:32:02,712 --> 00:32:04,923
What would an officer be doing

491
00:32:05,924 --> 00:32:08,843
in the place where you supposedly
kidnapped yourself?

492
00:32:09,510 --> 00:32:12,221
Well, if you’re saying he’s an officer,

493
00:32:12,847 --> 00:32:15,475
maybe he’s part of the search team.

494
00:32:16,476 --> 00:32:17,602
Search team?

495
00:32:18,186 --> 00:32:19,270
But he’s alone.

496
00:32:19,812 --> 00:32:21,189
Where’s the rest of his team?

497
00:32:21,648 --> 00:32:24,651
And I clearly heard him dial that number.

498
00:32:25,193 --> 00:32:26,945
It came from his phone.

499
00:32:27,487 --> 00:32:30,782
Why would he dial the same number
John Bautista dialed?

500
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:37,080
Sorry, I’m so lost
with all the names you’re mentioning.

501
00:32:37,747 --> 00:32:41,125
Number one,
what’s going on with that officer?

502
00:32:41,834 --> 00:32:46,255
Number two, what’s with
the Mary Had a Little Lamb tone?

503
00:32:46,798 --> 00:32:49,509
Out of all the options, why use that one?

504
00:32:50,259 --> 00:32:53,638
Number three, who is John Bautista?

505
00:32:54,055 --> 00:32:57,392
And number four, who is Moriarty?

506
00:32:59,852 --> 00:33:00,853
Go!

507
00:33:01,938 --> 00:33:02,939
Tell her.

508
00:33:04,482 --> 00:33:06,108
Do I really have to be the one to say it?

509
00:33:06,109 --> 00:33:07,986
It’s about time for her to know.

510
00:33:09,028 --> 00:33:12,031
You’re the chronicler of Q.E.D.,

511
00:33:13,449 --> 00:33:15,493
so you should be the one to tell her.

512
00:33:17,412 --> 00:33:18,454
Keep up.

513
00:33:19,330 --> 00:33:20,832
It’s a bit confusing.

514
00:33:25,294 --> 00:33:26,879
Where do I begin?

515
00:33:31,584 --> 00:33:33,918
It all began when I
joined the Q.E.D. Club.

516
00:33:35,346 --> 00:33:36,596
Is the one and only detective club...

517
00:33:36,597 --> 00:33:38,742
- in Clark University.
- I don’t know if it was just a coincidence.

518
00:33:38,766 --> 00:33:40,517
But the first case I witnessed.

519
00:33:40,518 --> 00:33:42,394
- The victim's name.
- is the Isaac Santino Murder case

520
00:33:42,395 --> 00:33:43,854
- is Isaac Santino.
- That happened in the chem lab.

521
00:33:43,855 --> 00:33:46,106
President of Lavoisier Club.

522
00:33:46,107 --> 00:33:48,109
Genesis Cabangon is the killer.

523
00:33:48,484 --> 00:33:51,778
- No. I didn't kill him.
- But when they caught Genesis,

524
00:33:51,779 --> 00:33:53,573
he suddenly died.

525
00:33:54,032 --> 00:33:56,492
But before he took his last breath,

526
00:33:56,826 --> 00:33:59,912
he managed to say, “Moriya...”

527
00:34:00,663 --> 00:34:01,663
Moriya...

528
00:34:02,457 --> 00:34:03,708
That's the first clue.

529
00:34:04,333 --> 00:34:05,792
The cases that followed

530
00:34:05,793 --> 00:34:07,837
weren’t related to Moriarty

531
00:34:08,046 --> 00:34:10,173
until Charles Meliton.

532
00:34:10,506 --> 00:34:13,383
Charles was blackmailing Clark U students

533
00:34:13,384 --> 00:34:16,386
using explicit photos that he has.

534
00:34:16,387 --> 00:34:18,847
But at the time, all we knew

535
00:34:18,848 --> 00:34:20,682
was that he had contact
with some mystery man

536
00:34:20,683 --> 00:34:22,268
providing those photos.

537
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:27,273
Then the Mylene, Michelle,
Madonna Missing Case.

538
00:34:27,523 --> 00:34:29,776
Where I ended up
becoming one of the victims.

539
00:34:30,068 --> 00:34:31,486
John Bautista?

540
00:34:36,657 --> 00:34:39,327
In this case,
the culprit was John Bautista.

541
00:34:39,535 --> 00:34:43,372
He used sodium hydroxide
to melt his victims’ bodies.

542
00:34:43,664 --> 00:34:46,918
This was the first time I heard
the Mary Had A Little Lamb tone.

543
00:34:47,168 --> 00:34:49,712
While I was inside the drum,
he made a phone call.

544
00:34:53,716 --> 00:34:56,302
Just like Genesis, when John got caught,

545
00:34:56,969 --> 00:34:58,763
he suddenly died too.

546
00:34:59,388 --> 00:35:02,390
But he managed to mention
Moriarty’s full name.

547
00:35:02,391 --> 00:35:03,476
Moriarty.

548
00:35:06,354 --> 00:35:08,064
And that’s how they were connected.

549
00:35:08,481 --> 00:35:12,527
The chemical Genesis stole
was sodium hydroxide

550
00:35:12,735 --> 00:35:14,695
for John Bautista.

551
00:35:15,738 --> 00:35:18,115
- I have a student.
- And then there was the Stein Alberts missing case.

552
00:35:18,116 --> 00:35:20,367
- Stein Alberts.
- Monica Segundo admitted

553
00:35:20,368 --> 00:35:22,494
that she was the one who asked her genie

554
00:35:22,495 --> 00:35:24,246
to kidnap Stein,

555
00:35:24,247 --> 00:35:26,582
her rival in the Math contest.

556
00:35:27,166 --> 00:35:28,416
She also confessed

557
00:35:28,417 --> 00:35:30,962
that this genie was someone named “M.”

558
00:35:32,046 --> 00:35:34,799
I don't want! Forgive me!

559
00:35:35,341 --> 00:35:37,551
The last is the Belladonna Case

560
00:35:37,552 --> 00:35:41,639
where Catherine, Justin, Serena...

561
00:35:42,098 --> 00:35:43,808
and even Loki became victims.

562
00:35:48,354 --> 00:35:50,355
Loki! Loki!

563
00:35:50,356 --> 00:35:52,525
The culprit is Daniel Geronimo.

564
00:35:54,861 --> 00:35:58,280
Who we later discovered
had been contacting Charles Meliton

565
00:35:58,281 --> 00:36:01,616
for explicit photos
to blackmail the victims

566
00:36:01,617 --> 00:36:04,620
into drinking tea laced with belladonna.

567
00:36:05,079 --> 00:36:07,039
Every culprit I mentioned

568
00:36:07,540 --> 00:36:10,168
was connected to M or Moriarty.

569
00:36:12,753 --> 00:36:15,380
I know it’s information overload,

570
00:36:15,381 --> 00:36:18,676
but I’m sure you can keep up.

571
00:36:18,926 --> 00:36:21,804
I mean, you do have a photographic memory.

572
00:36:22,889 --> 00:36:24,640
Why would M do this?

573
00:36:25,558 --> 00:36:29,228
To be honest,
we’re not sure about his true intentions.

574
00:36:29,937 --> 00:36:31,355
But what I do know is,

575
00:36:31,814 --> 00:36:35,234
this Moriarty, likes to play games.

576
00:36:37,028 --> 00:36:40,698
I can’t believe someone like that
actually exists in this school.

577
00:36:41,157 --> 00:36:45,953
I thought it was just a coincidence
that students get hurt every other week.

578
00:36:47,288 --> 00:36:49,957
So there’s really someone behind all this.

579
00:36:52,084 --> 00:36:54,295
That’s how dangerous this club is.

580
00:36:55,087 --> 00:36:57,548
We don’t know who the next target is.

581
00:36:58,174 --> 00:37:00,801
But you can still back out.

582
00:37:00,885 --> 00:37:01,886
Back out?

583
00:37:02,386 --> 00:37:04,055
Why would I back out?

584
00:37:04,847 --> 00:37:06,556
I’m even more interested now

585
00:37:06,557 --> 00:37:10,228
because we’ve got
a big bad guy to take down.

586
00:37:10,561 --> 00:37:12,897
Feels like we’ve got a grand mission here.

587
00:37:13,481 --> 00:37:16,275
So going back to the rookie officer,

588
00:37:16,776 --> 00:37:19,237
maybe he’s connected to the mastermind?

589
00:37:19,779 --> 00:37:21,280
Just as I thought...

590
00:37:23,366 --> 00:37:25,618
that person is connected to Moriarty.

591
00:37:25,952 --> 00:37:28,037
Do you really suspect him?

592
00:37:29,455 --> 00:37:31,666
I know you noticed it too, Lorelei.

593
00:37:31,958 --> 00:37:33,758
You're just not really
paying attention to it.

594
00:37:34,710 --> 00:37:36,587
Remember during belladona case?

595
00:37:37,421 --> 00:37:38,339
Officer Montreal.

596
00:37:38,364 --> 00:37:39,710
- Good afternoon.
- Gave us the report on the victims

597
00:37:39,735 --> 00:37:40,428
around lunchtime.

598
00:37:40,453 --> 00:37:42,735
Chief Gareth asked
me to hand this over...

599
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:45,805
Daniel Geronimo walked
into our clubroom moments later,

600
00:37:46,389 --> 00:37:49,140
as if the rookie officer's
delivery of the files

601
00:37:49,141 --> 00:37:51,352
was his cue to challenge me.

602
00:37:51,894 --> 00:37:53,145
Very good.

603
00:37:54,063 --> 00:37:56,732
Then, when you were taken to the hospital,

604
00:37:57,191 --> 00:38:01,445
Officer Montreal brought us
the autopsy report too.

605
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:06,033
Could he have gone there
to check on your condition?

606
00:38:06,909 --> 00:38:11,414
It's possible Moriarty sent an agent
who we’d least suspect.

607
00:38:12,206 --> 00:38:13,749
And there’s this other guy.

608
00:38:15,251 --> 00:38:16,294
What’s his name?

609
00:38:16,794 --> 00:38:19,005
The one who liquifies his victims?

610
00:38:19,255 --> 00:38:21,299
- It's John Bautista.
- John Bautista!

611
00:38:22,508 --> 00:38:25,386
He was poisoned while in police custody.

612
00:38:26,178 --> 00:38:27,179
John!

613
00:38:29,056 --> 00:38:33,519
We talked about the possibility
that someone from campus police did it.

614
00:38:34,687 --> 00:38:36,063
Connect the dots,

615
00:38:36,439 --> 00:38:38,858
and they’ll point you to Officer Montreal.

616
00:38:39,650 --> 00:38:43,154
And yet, we don't have concrete evidence

617
00:38:43,362 --> 00:38:45,823
to connect him to Moriarty.

618
00:38:45,990 --> 00:38:49,784
And why was he at the gym yesterday

619
00:38:49,785 --> 00:38:52,496
if he had nothing to do
with your kidnapping?

620
00:38:52,830 --> 00:38:54,457
You reported it to the police, right?

621
00:38:55,291 --> 00:38:57,335
He found out and followed you.

622
00:38:57,626 --> 00:38:58,669
We don’t know.

623
00:39:00,046 --> 00:39:01,172
You have a point.

624
00:39:02,131 --> 00:39:03,299
But, wait...

625
00:39:04,967 --> 00:39:07,762
why didn’t you tell me
about this information?

626
00:39:08,763 --> 00:39:10,973
Why did you withhold this from me?

627
00:39:11,974 --> 00:39:14,060
It wasn’t confirmed back then.

628
00:39:14,602 --> 00:39:16,062
It was just a hunch.

629
00:39:16,520 --> 00:39:18,314
And if I had told you about it,

630
00:39:18,731 --> 00:39:22,068
you might have acted strange
in his presence.

631
00:39:23,361 --> 00:39:26,029
So you think,
that I would be stupid enough

632
00:39:26,030 --> 00:39:28,032
to act suspiciously in front of him?

633
00:39:28,074 --> 00:39:29,325
Is that what you’re saying?

634
00:39:30,951 --> 00:39:32,620
Better to be safe than sorry.

635
00:39:34,747 --> 00:39:35,748
Guys?

636
00:39:36,082 --> 00:39:40,711
Nevertheless, we’re already
two steps ahead of Moriarty.

637
00:39:41,462 --> 00:39:44,090
We've already identified
one of his minions.

638
00:39:44,627 --> 00:39:48,427
And we've got a hint
on how to divine his phone number.

639
00:39:49,111 --> 00:39:52,264
And if we can manage
to get closer to Officer Montreal,

640
00:39:52,473 --> 00:39:56,142
we might find the thread
that will lead us exactly

641
00:39:56,143 --> 00:39:57,770
to that mastermind.

642
00:40:03,442 --> 00:40:04,527
Why?

643
00:40:05,653 --> 00:40:06,654
What is it?

644
00:40:06,987 --> 00:40:11,117
Didn’t you say you heard the ringtone
outside the gym?

645
00:40:11,700 --> 00:40:12,701
Yes.

646
00:40:12,827 --> 00:40:14,995
You probably still remember it, right?

647
00:40:16,122 --> 00:40:18,915
Can you figure out the number combination

648
00:40:18,916 --> 00:40:22,294
that produces
the Mary Had a Little Lamb tone?

649
00:40:23,087 --> 00:40:25,672
It’s too challenging to distinguish

650
00:40:25,673 --> 00:40:28,968
which numbers produced the sound I heard.

651
00:40:29,510 --> 00:40:31,637
They’re all pretty much the same.

652
00:40:32,388 --> 00:40:36,100
Obviously, zero and nine
are the first numbers to come up.

653
00:40:36,392 --> 00:40:37,643
Listen to this.

654
00:40:43,357 --> 00:40:47,194
The first four numbers
are from As White as Snow.

655
00:40:52,491 --> 00:40:57,746
And the next seven numbers
are part of Ma-ry-had-a-lit-tle-lamb.

656
00:40:58,456 --> 00:41:02,793
If we follow that tone,
this is the number that comes out.

657
00:41:25,274 --> 00:41:29,194
But that’s not the only number
that can generate

658
00:41:29,195 --> 00:41:31,655
the Mary Had a Little Lamb tune.

659
00:41:32,364 --> 00:41:33,908
It could also be something like this.

660
00:41:55,346 --> 00:42:00,059
It seems we’ll need to lean
on Moriarty's campus police insider.

661
00:42:00,726 --> 00:42:03,645
If he has a list of numbers
in his call log,

662
00:42:03,646 --> 00:42:07,233
the one matching that melody
is the phone number we’re looking for.

663
00:42:08,067 --> 00:42:09,068
Wait.

664
00:42:09,401 --> 00:42:11,737
We’re gonna steal Montreal’s phone?

665
00:42:12,196 --> 00:42:14,490
If that's the only way
to extract the information.

666
00:42:14,782 --> 00:42:15,866
But, Loki...

667
00:42:30,005 --> 00:42:31,549
Who could it be?

668
00:42:55,406 --> 00:42:56,907
Officer Montreal.

669
00:43:13,215 --> 00:43:15,634
Can I just go with you instead, Loki?

670
00:43:16,260 --> 00:43:19,680
I’ll learn a lot more if I go with you.

671
00:43:19,930 --> 00:43:22,308
I need to learn from the best!

672
00:43:24,893 --> 00:43:25,894
Hi!

673
00:43:27,438 --> 00:43:28,647
We’re not lost.

674
00:43:33,694 --> 00:43:34,695
Thank you.

675
00:44:04,475 --> 00:44:06,075
Is this what you’re looking for, Nestor?
